## Pre-built Component Classes

Use these in JSX `className` props directly:

```jsx
// Buttons
<button className="sf-btn-primary">Schedule</button>
<button className="sf-btn-secondary">Cancel</button>
<button className="sf-btn-ghost">View Details</button>

// Status badges
<span className="sf-badge-success">Completed</span>
<span className="sf-badge-warning">⚠ Warning</span>
<span className="sf-badge-error">Overdue</span>
<span className="sf-badge-info">Scheduled</span>

// Form inputs
<label className="sf-label">Account Name</label>
<input className="sf-input" type="text" placeholder="Search..." />
<select className="sf-select">...</select>

// Data table
<table className="sf-table">
  <thead><tr><th>Account ID</th><th>Status</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>             {/* normal row */}
    <tr className="selected">  {/* selected row — blue tint */}
    <tr className="warning">   {/* warning row — amber tint */}
  </tbody>
</table>

// Cards
<div className="sf-card">
  <div className="sf-card-header">Service Appointments</div>
  <div className="sf-card-body">...</div>
</div>

// Avatar / Resource icon
<span className="sf-avatar">CT</span>   {/* 32px */}
<span className="sf-avatar-lg">CT</span> {/* 40px */}

// Page shell
<nav className="sf-topnav">...</nav>
<div className="sf-subnav">
  <button className="sf-subnav-tab active">Gantt</button>
  <button className="sf-subnav-tab">Map</button>
</div>
```

---

## Typography Scale

Always use `text-sf-*` classes, not default Tailwind text sizes:

```
text-sf-xs   → 11px  badges, timestamps
text-sf-sm   → 12px  helper text, captions  
text-sf-base → 13px  body text, table cells  ← DEFAULT
text-sf-md   → 14px  secondary labels
text-sf-lg   → 16px  section headers
text-sf-xl   → 18px  page titles
text-sf-2xl  → 22px  modal headings
```

---

## Layout Heights

Use named height tokens for consistent component sizing:
```
h-sf-input      → 32px  standard inputs
h-sf-button     → 32px  buttons
h-sf-topnav     → 48px  app header
h-sf-subnav     → 44px  tab bar
h-sf-row        → 36px  list rows
h-sf-gantt-row  → 48px  Gantt resource rows
```

---

## Spacing (4px grid)

```
p-sf-1 / m-sf-1  → 4px
p-sf-2 / m-sf-2  → 8px
p-sf-3 / m-sf-3  → 12px
p-sf-4 / m-sf-4  → 16px
p-sf-6 / m-sf-6  → 24px
p-sf-8 / m-sf-8  → 32px
```

---

## Utilization Pill Pattern

```jsx
function UtilPill({ pct }: { pct: number }) {
  const cls = pct > 95 ? 'sf-util-pill-high'
            : pct > 80 ? 'sf-util-pill-medium'
            :             'sf-util-pill-low'
  return <span className={cls}>Utilization: {pct}%</span>
}
```

---

## Don't Do This

```jsx
// ❌ Hardcoded colors
<div style={{ background: '#4BCA81' }}>

// ❌ Arbitrary Tailwind values  
<div className="bg-[#0176D3] text-[13px]">

// ❌ Default Tailwind colors for status
<span className="bg-green-100 text-green-800">Completed</span>

// ❌ Wrong font size token
<p className="text-sm">  // use text-sf-base instead

// ✅ Correct patterns
<div style={{ background: 'var(--sf-gantt-appointment)' }}>
<div className="bg-sf-brand text-sf-text-inverse">
<span className="sf-badge-success">Completed</span>
<p className="text-sf-base">
```
